was not so well attended.

182
00:15:03,820 --> 00:15:07,908
It would appear that media attention is
always focusing on the negatives in Baltimore,

183
00:15:07,991 --> 00:15:10,744
but you aren't around
when we're making real progress.

184
00:15:10,827 --> 00:15:12,787
Nevertheless, I'm glad to see
so many of you here.

185
00:15:12,829 --> 00:15:15,290
Some of you representing
not just our local media,

186
00:15:15,373 --> 00:15:17,167
but national attention to this problem.

187
00:15:17,250 --> 00:15:20,420
Thank you for caring enough
about our most vulnerable citizens

188
00:15:20,504 --> 00:15:22,422
to address yourselves to this tragedy.

189
00:15:22,506 --> 00:15:26,676
Our homeless citizens, those who have
fallen through the cracks of our society,

190
00:15:26,927 --> 00:15:30,597
those who command
the least of our attentions and efforts,

191
00:15:30,680 --> 00:15:33,767
they seemingly have little to endear
themselves to politicians.

192
00:15:33,850 --> 00:15:37,104
They don't vote, by and large.
They don't contribute to campaigns.

193
00:15:37,187 --> 00:15:39,106
They offer little to a city's tax base,

194
00:15:39,189 --> 00:15:42,025
and to the extent that our government
is made aware of their existence,

195
00:15:42,109 --> 00:15:45,362
it responds by trying to mitigate
the damage done by their presence.

196
00:15:45,570 --> 00:15:48,782
We open a food bank here, a shelter there.

197
00:15:48,865 --> 00:15:50,784
We try to move them away from downtown,

198
00:15:50,867 --> 00:15:55,038
away from our communal areas,
away from our schools, away from our homes.

199
00:15:55,122 --> 00:15:56,849
If you were to judge our society
by the manner

200
00:15:56,873 --> 00:15:58,708
in which we treat
those lost on our streets,

201
00:15:58,959 --> 00:16:01,169
we would have cause to be shamed.

202
00:16:01,253 --> 00:16:03,964
Well, I am, god forgive me, a politician.

203
00:16:05,173 --> 00:16:09,886
But I ran for public office because I believe
that there is a different way of governing.

204
00:16:09,970 --> 00:16:13,932
And I believe that in the end we will be
judged not by the efforts we make on behalf

205
00:16:14,015 --> 00:16:16,726
of those who vote for us,
who contribute to our campaigns,

206
00:16:16,810 --> 00:16:18,854
or those who provide for our tax base.

207
00:16:18,937 --> 00:16:22,816
I believe that we will bejudged by what we
provide to the weakest and most vulnerable.

208
00:16:22,899 --> 00:16:25,735
That is the test. That is my test.

209
00:16:26,611 --> 00:16:30,323
Somebody is killing homeless
men in this city.

210
00:16:30,407 --> 00:16:34,327
Taking the lives of fellow citizens
who do not have the means or the strength

211
00:16:34,411 --> 00:16:37,622
to properly protect themselves.
They will be stopped.

212
00:16:37,706 --> 00:16:41,835
We will do everything in our power
to stop them. You have my word on this.

213
00:16:45,380 --> 00:16:47,007
Thank you, Mr. Mayor.

214
00:16:47,090 --> 00:16:49,759
- What got into you?
- What?

215
00:16:49,843 --> 00:16:53,722
I want to assure the public that we are
doing everything possible in our power

216
00:16:53,805 --> 00:16:55,140
to apprehend this subject.

217
00:16:55,223 --> 00:16:57,184
Homicide detectives are working
around the clock.

218
00:16:57,267 --> 00:17:01,855
District officers are in contact with the
agencies that work with the homeless.

219
00:17:01,938 --> 00:17:07,694
