but, with that caveat, I will take questions.

220
00:17:09,112 --> 00:17:10,906
Commissioner, is there any connection

221
00:17:10,989 --> 00:17:14,034
between these murders and those
in the vacant homes last year?

222
00:17:14,159 --> 00:17:15,702
No connection.

223
00:17:16,745 --> 00:17:20,832
Commissioner, are you asking the FBI
to join in the investigation?

224
00:17:20,916 --> 00:17:25,128
I think deputy commissioner Daniels
is in a position to elaborate on that.

225
00:17:32,928 --> 00:17:35,138
We'll take whatever help is offered.

226
00:17:35,222 --> 00:17:39,392
Our detectives will work closely with
the behavioral analysis unit at Quantico...

227
00:17:39,476 --> 00:17:42,187
Deputy, even with all the resources
at your disposal,

228
00:17:42,270 --> 00:17:44,981
isn't it extremely difficult
to catch a serial killer?

229
00:17:45,273 --> 00:17:49,069
Our ability to secure genetic material
and the growing DNA data bank

230
00:17:49,152 --> 00:17:51,738
are assets unavailable
to us even a few years ago.

231
00:17:51,821 --> 00:17:53,657
Our ability to effectively use resources

232
00:17:53,740 --> 00:17:56,618
has been increased with the aid
of sophisticated computer software.

233
00:17:56,952 --> 00:18:00,747
And we have some of the best criminal
investigators in the nation working 24/7.

234
00:18:01,081 --> 00:18:06,169
As the mayor made very clear a moment ago,
this is now a priority for the department.

235
00:18:07,379 --> 00:18:09,099
Has a note been found at any of the scenes?

236
00:18:09,506 --> 00:18:13,510
I'm not at Liberty to go into any details
of the investigation at this time.

237
00:18:21,851 --> 00:18:23,728
You want me to hang?

238
00:18:39,536 --> 00:18:41,329
He told you who I am, right?

239
00:18:44,291 --> 00:18:49,337
Son, the thing about murder
is it never goes off the books.

240
00:18:49,546 --> 00:18:52,465
I mean, we work on 'em
for weeks, months, years.

241
00:18:52,716 --> 00:18:57,554
We keep on with it until finally
someone decides they've had enough,

242
00:18:57,804 --> 00:19:01,891
until we get the right word
from the right person.

243
00:19:01,975 --> 00:19:03,977
And you know what happens then?

244
00:19:12,736 --> 00:19:14,738
When a case does go down...

245
00:19:16,239 --> 00:19:20,535
All those people who kept quiet about it,
who lied about it,

246
00:19:20,618 --> 00:19:22,829
all of them who thought
it wasn't coming back on 'em,

247
00:19:23,204 --> 00:19:27,584
they end up catchin' a charge.
And they get time behind that.

248
00:19:28,752 --> 00:19:31,671
Time, huh? You gonna give me time?

249
00:19:41,181 --> 00:19:44,017
If you know something
about that boy Lex getting shot,

250
00:19:44,100 --> 00:19:46,353
now is your last chance to speak to that.

251
00:19:48,271 --> 00:19:52,275
- You gave a statement last year...
- Why don't you promise to get me outta here?

252
00:19:53,109 --> 00:19:55,945
That's what y'all do, ain't it?
Lie to dumb-ass niggers?

253
00:20:01,409 --> 00:20:05,121
Yo, y'all need to get this police
out my face before I bank his ass.

254
00:20:17,967 --> 00:20:20,804
You're a natural, kiddo.
You had 'em eating out of your hand.

255
00:20:20,887 --> 00:20:24,891
Shit, I was just following the mayor's
lead. He wants a full-court press, right?

256
00:20:29,270 --> 00:20:30,897
We can add a detective or two.

257
00:20:30,980 --> 00:20:34,692
And you can ask patrol to concentrate
on posts where vagrants congregate.

258
00:20:34,776 --> 00:20:37,779
But other than that, deputy,
the cupboard is bare.

259
00:20:37,862 --> 00:20:39,364
- But carcetti...
- Make no mistake.

260
00:20:39,447 --> 00:20:43,410
He wants us to solve the murders.
He just doesn't want it to cost.

261
00:20:44,327 --> 00:20:45,954
Don't look so shocked.

262
00:20:46,037 --> 00:20:48,706
You're runnin' with the big dogs now. Heh.

263
00:20:50,458 --> 00:20:52,919
Isn't it enough that we're
up on the killer's cell phone?

264
00:20:53,002 --> 00:20:55,171
Couldn't you track him on the GPS chip?

265
00:20:55,255 --> 00:21:00,009
He's using a burner and we suspect he's
taking out the battery between calls.

266
00:21:00,093 --> 00:21:02,512
And there's nothing to stop him
from changing phones,

267
00:21:02,846 --> 00:21:04,597
calling the reporter from a new number.

268
00:21:04,681 --> 00:21:07,058
So you want to tap
the reporter's phone as well?

269
00:21:07,142 --> 00:21:10,854
It stands to reason that we should monitor
this thing from both ends.

270
00:21:10,937 --> 00:21:14,149
- It's what we would normally do.
- Nothing about this is normal.

271
00:21:14,232 --> 00:21:17,026
A Baltimore sun reporter's phone
is problematic.

272
00:21:17,193 --> 00:21:20,613
We need to strike a balance
between your needs as investigators

273
00:21:20,697 --> 00:21:23,116
and the first amendment rights of the sun
and its sources.

274
00:21:23,199 --> 00:21:26,828
The first amendment does not
guarantee privacy, your honor.

275
00:21:26,911 --> 00:21:28,872
Legal precedent clearly indicates...

276
00:21:28,955 --> 00:21:31,207
- Look, I'm not saying that we can't, but...
- But what?

277
00:21:34,836 --> 00:21:39,549
Until we get the sense
that your suspect is changing phones,

278
00:21:40,049 --> 00:21:43,136
I'm not inclined to look
with favor on tapping

279
00:21:43,219 --> 00:21:45,972
the Baltimore sun's telecommunications.

280
00:21:46,055 --> 00:21:48,075
- We're afraid to piss them off?
- Never pick a fight

281
00:21:48,099 --> 00:21:50,602
with anyone who buys ink by the barrelful.

282
00:21:51,853 --> 00:21:54,105
- Christ.
- Very well, judge.

283
00:22:02,947 --> 00:22:05,116
How many enemies do you need?

284
00:22:08,661 --> 00:22:09,996
Deputy.

285
00:22:26,804 --> 00:22:29,474
- Where did you get all this?
- Darling, you do not want to know.

286
00:22:35,897 --> 00:22:38,274
What's up with you?

287
00:22:38,358 --> 00:22:40,318
Got all 22 out of the drawer?

288
00:22:40,401 --> 00:22:43,112
- Workin' the whole mess at once.
- I'm trying to see 'em fresh.

289
00:22:45,073 --> 00:22:48,701
25. My triple.
It comes back to Mario and his people.

290
00:22:48,785 --> 00:22:50,161
For sure?

291
00:22:50,245 --> 00:22:52,205
A good informant tells me so.

292
00:22:52,288 --> 00:22:56,292
Says one of my vics was talking bad
about Mr. Stanfield, who took it personal.

293
00:22:56,626 --> 00:22:58,419
Killed him, his girl, his muscle.

294
00:22:58,628 --> 00:23:01,548
Left the little kids alive,
so I guess he ain't all bad.

295
00:23:01,631 --> 00:23:03,591
People out there
so scared of this motherfucker,

296
00:23:03,675 --> 00:23:05,595
I can't get close to an
eyewitness on any of it.

297
00:23:09,055 --> 00:23:12,058
- Where you at with the rest of these cases?
- We don't even have lab work

298
00:23:12,141 --> 00:23:13,768
on 14 of these bodies.

299
00:23:13,851 --> 00:23:16,205
A year later I'm still walking in
written requests to landsman,

300
00:23:16,229 --> 00:23:17,981
who just files them away in his drawer.

301
00:23:18,064 --> 00:23:20,066
Mcnulty would've called a news reporter.

302
00:23:20,149 --> 00:23:22,318
I am not him.

303
00:23:22,402 --> 00:23:26,906
Well, what would the bunk do?
Take no for a fucking answer?

304
00:23:29,158 --> 00:23:31,911
We had cutbacks, you know that.

305
00:23:31,995 --> 00:23:35,832
We lost three or four trace examiners.
Lost half our clerical.

306
00:23:35,915 --> 00:23:38,710
The freezer went bad,
we lost four months of blood samples.

307
00:23:38,793 --> 00:23:40,878
Did you know that? Four months of evidence

308
00:23:40,962 --> 00:23:43,423
and they still haven't replaced
my damn icebox.

309
00:23:43,506 --> 00:23:45,550
My heart pumps purple piss for you.

310
00:23:45,633 --> 00:23:48,261
Now, I got the worst mass murder
in b-more history

311
00:23:48,344 --> 00:23:52,348
and you can't get the trace work back to me
inside of a year? C'mon, Ron...

312
00:23:52,640 --> 00:23:54,183
Look...

313
00:23:55,018 --> 00:23:56,769
You can't go to the press.

314
00:23:56,853 --> 00:24:01,107
I mean, heads will roll if this gets out.
It isn't anyone's fault.

315
00:24:01,190 --> 00:24:03,901
In fact, it's a little
bit on you, i-in a way.

316
00:24:03,985 --> 00:24:05,695
The fuck you say?

317
00:24:06,654 --> 00:24:10,908
After Annette took retirement, the casework
got backed up worse than ever, right?

318
00:24:11,117 --> 00:24:13,703
Well, we put in to fill
the lab assistant slot,

319
00:24:13,786 --> 00:24:16,181
but with the cutbacks,
the best they could give us was a temp.

320
00:24:16,205 --> 00:24:19,500
- A temp?
- Yeah. No medical. No pension.

321
00:24:19,584 --> 00:24:22,795
A temp hire to get us over for a while.

322
00:24:22,879 --> 00:24:25,632
Come on, I'll show you something.

323
00:24:25,715 --> 00:24:29,844
She was assigned to sort and file
the individual trace elements...

324
00:24:29,927 --> 00:24:31,929
Hair, fiber mostly...

325
00:24:33,723 --> 00:24:36,726
You know, from each of the 14 scenes.

326
00:24:38,770 --> 00:24:39,979
So what's the problem?

327
00:24:40,063 --> 00:24:44,233
In the initial papennork,
you wrote out all 22 cc numbers, right?

328
00:24:44,317 --> 00:24:46,277
- Right.
- But in the supplemental requests,

329
00:24:46,361 --> 00:24:48,988
you put all the incidents
under the initial cc

330
00:24:49,072 --> 00:24:51,699
and then you wrote, "et al," remember?

331
00:24:51,783 --> 00:24:54,994
- So?
- She didn't know what "et al" meant.

332
00:24:55,078 --> 00:24:58,331
And she sorted everything under
the single complaint number.

333
00:24:58,414 --> 00:25:00,124
- You don't fucking mean...
- Yeah.

334
00:25:00,208 --> 00:25:03,294
We have no idea which one of your scenes
any of this shit came from.

335
00:25:03,378 --> 00:25:06,255
- Oh...
- We don't have a clue.

336
00:25:11,719 --> 00:25:16,140
Actually, except for this
she's been a pretty good employee.

337
00:25:27,777 --> 00:25:30,196
- Surveillance teams.
- Two each on 12-hour shifts.

338
00:25:30,279 --> 00:25:32,759
I need them to set up on certain locations
common to our cases.

339
00:25:34,242 --> 00:25:36,953
C'mon, Jay. You heard the mayor.
This case is a redball.

340
00:25:37,036 --> 00:25:39,872
That it is. You can
have greggs, if you want.

341
00:25:39,956 --> 00:25:42,796
The last time I offered her up, you
kicked her back to her own casework.

342
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:45,837
Other than a second detective,
you are on your own.

343
00:25:48,631 --> 00:25:50,216
- So it's all bullshit.
- Idunno.

344
00:25:50,299 --> 00:25:52,468
I thought the mayor
gave a very nice speech.

345
00:25:52,635 --> 00:25:55,972
I, for one, was moved. Much like
the bull to which you just referred.

346
00:26:07,859 --> 00:26:09,652
- Tell you one thing...
- What's that?

347
00:26:09,736 --> 00:26:12,613
Motherfucker whose got the connect,
he the one that did Joe.

348
00:26:13,030 --> 00:26:14,657
Oh, no doubt.

349
00:26:30,965 --> 00:26:35,428
Y'all know the co-op took some hits.
Joe. Hungry man.

350
00:26:35,511 --> 00:26:39,807
Good people, especially Joe.
Their passin' was for real, cold-blooded.

351
00:26:40,183 --> 00:26:43,144
I know what you thinkin',
so I'm-a put it out there...

352
00:26:44,479 --> 00:26:46,355
I'm responsible.

353
00:26:48,858 --> 00:26:51,527
A week or so back,
I made a move on Omar, with Joe's approval.

354
00:26:51,736 --> 00:26:55,072
The fagot ain't had heart enough to come
at me, so he come at those close to me.

355
00:26:55,156 --> 00:26:57,742
Now I'm doublin' the bounty.

356
00:26:57,825 --> 00:27:01,120
Hundred large for a whiff of that dicksuck.

357
00:27:01,204 --> 00:27:03,623
Two hundred fifty for his head.

358
00:27:03,706 --> 00:27:06,793
- What about the connect?
- I got that covered.

359
00:27:06,876 --> 00:27:10,838
And in light of that fact, I'm-a take
it upon myself to conduct this meet.

360
00:27:12,215 --> 00:27:15,676
Slim, I want you take over
hungry man's slice of the cake.

361
00:27:16,219 --> 00:27:20,640
Meanin' no disrespect,
but I ain't cut out to be no ceo.

362
00:27:25,311 --> 00:27:28,981
- Cheese, then.
- No problem, man. Got you covered.

363
00:27:29,065 --> 00:27:33,277
Until we settle up with Omar,
I think it's best we suspend these meets.

364
00:27:33,361 --> 00:27:35,655
In fact, I ain't really
one for meets nohow.

365
00:27:35,738 --> 00:27:39,283
Anybody got a problem here on out,
bring it to me, or sit on that shit.

366
00:27:39,367 --> 00:27:44,664
Those of you on the westside
who need to re-up, holler at my man monk.

367
00:27:44,747 --> 00:27:48,417
He gonna handle supply over there.
On the eastside, cheese.

368
00:27:48,584 --> 00:27:50,336
One more thing.

369
00:27:50,419 --> 00:27:52,839
Price of the brick going up.

370
00:27:52,922 --> 00:27:54,590
Thirty more.

371
00:27:56,968 --> 00:27:58,511
All right. Enough of this shit.

372
00:28:13,776 --> 00:28:15,319
What?

373
00:28:15,403 --> 00:28:17,780
Next year for the schools.
From now until December,

374
00:28:17,864 --> 00:28:21,075
we're all about the plight of the homeless.
The great whiting has spoken.

375
00:28:21,158 --> 00:28:24,787
I appealed to klebanow half an hour ago
but he gave me the thumbs down. I'm sorry.

376
00:28:28,457 --> 00:28:32,503
Check it out, people.
Our Metro desk has some national profile.

377
00:28:33,421 --> 00:28:37,550
We're being careful to cooperate
with the investigators in every way.

378
00:28:37,633 --> 00:28:41,053
My newspaper has no desire to get between
the police and the suspect.

379
00:28:41,137 --> 00:28:45,016
But still, wouldn't you agree it's
an incredible moment for anyjournalist

380
00:28:45,099 --> 00:28:49,061
to come face to face with that type
of pure evil like the son of Sam?

381
00:28:49,145 --> 00:28:52,440
That makes you the
Jimmy breslin of Baltimore.

382
00:28:52,523 --> 00:28:54,901
Well, no, iwouldn't say that. I mean...

383
00:28:54,984 --> 00:28:58,446
But knowing you have been
in contact with a killer,

384
00:28:58,529 --> 00:29:02,033
are you at all concerned about continuing
to report from the street?

385
00:29:02,116 --> 00:29:04,952
No, not at all. I mean, this is what we do.

386
00:29:05,036 --> 00:29:08,456
As a reporter, you expect to be
in harm's way at some points.

387
00:29:08,539 --> 00:29:10,917
- It's what we do.
- Agreed. It's what you do.

388
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:15,922
But very rarely does a reporter end up
being in the middle of a story -

389
00:29:16,005 --> 00:29:17,757
an ongoing story -

390
00:29:17,840 --> 00:29:23,679
about a murderer who is still at large and
posing a severe and deadly risk to the...

391
00:29:24,680 --> 00:29:27,099
You shoulda heard phelan this morning.

392
00:29:27,183 --> 00:29:31,437
Too scared to tap the newspaper phones
they might shit on him for it.

393
00:29:32,104 --> 00:29:33,814
Fuckin' hackjudge.

394
00:29:33,898 --> 00:29:36,484
What would you want with more wires?
We got all we need.

395
00:29:36,567 --> 00:29:39,487
I don't want another wire.
It's the principle of the thing...

396
00:29:39,570 --> 00:29:41,656
It just pissed me off listening to him.

397
00:29:42,907 --> 00:29:45,785
Oh, yeah, no surveillance cars.

398
00:29:46,911 --> 00:29:49,205
They won't go beyond me and greggs.

399
00:29:49,872 --> 00:29:53,668
You and sydnor will have to work it
as best you can for right now.

400
00:29:53,751 --> 00:29:55,252
Assholes.

401
00:30:00,257 --> 00:30:02,259
They need another body, don't they?

402
00:30:04,929 --> 00:30:07,098
I'll call our man in the southern.

403
00:30:15,189 --> 00:30:17,149
I can take it from here.
Y'all can bounce.

404
00:30:17,233 --> 00:30:18,818
All right, boss.

405
00:30:27,868 --> 00:30:29,578
What up, Rick?

406
00:30:29,662 --> 00:30:31,205
Just like ol' times for me and you.

407
00:30:31,288 --> 00:30:35,751
- Whatever you want it's yours, all right?
- Tonight, I'm just gonna take yo' jump...

408
00:30:38,170 --> 00:30:40,589
- And leave you with a little something.
- What's that?

409
00:30:40,673 --> 00:30:42,216
My word in your ear.

410
00:30:42,299 --> 00:30:44,593
I'm callin' marlo a straight bitch.

411
00:30:45,720 --> 00:30:48,723
I'm sayin' it don't take much
to shoot down a blind man.

412
00:30:49,557 --> 00:30:53,519
And as for him steppin' to me,
you tell that dude he ain't got the heart.

413
00:30:53,602 --> 00:30:54,812
All right.

414
00:30:54,895 --> 00:30:58,065
You tell that man I'm
in the street, waiting.

415
00:30:58,149 --> 00:31:01,110
Just like a little bitch,
he ain't nowhere to be found.

416
00:31:01,193 --> 00:31:02,862
I'll tell him. I will.

417
00:31:04,697 --> 00:31:06,866
Pick up your keys and go on inside, yo.

418
00:31:14,999 --> 00:31:16,500
You kill Joe?

419
00:31:16,584 --> 00:31:18,711
Hungry?

420
00:31:20,713 --> 00:31:22,423
Didn't think so.

421
00:31:32,308 --> 00:31:34,143
What now?

422
00:31:34,935 --> 00:31:37,188
There's more than one way to skin a case.

423
00:31:49,158 --> 00:31:50,701
Already ran them for priors, right?

424
00:31:51,202 --> 00:31:54,246
Priors, yeah. But I'm gonna run
every name you guys developed

425
00:31:54,330 --> 00:31:55,748
through the entire database.

426
00:31:55,998 --> 00:31:59,627
Not just for priors, but for
anything at all in the miles system.

427
00:31:59,710 --> 00:32:02,588
Court appearances, parole, probation,

428
00:32:02,671 --> 00:32:05,091
gun permits, doc, open bails.

429
00:32:05,174 --> 00:32:09,720
- You're playing long shots, huh?
- Darlin', I'm playin' the hand I've been dealt.

430
00:32:10,721 --> 00:32:11,972
An h-file?

431
00:32:18,479 --> 00:32:21,148
- Who caught the case?
- Worden. Other shift.

432
00:32:21,232 --> 00:32:23,442
Stepfather. Beaten to death.

433
00:32:24,068 --> 00:32:28,656
They interviewed the mother,
but no one else in the household.

434
00:32:29,573 --> 00:32:31,784
Doesn't exactly fit
with the others, does it?

435
00:32:31,867 --> 00:32:34,995
A straight-up ass-whoopin' in an alley
doesn't seem like marlo Stanfield.

436
00:32:35,079 --> 00:32:38,040
- No, it doesn't.
- But you're gonna work it anyway.

437
00:32:40,626 --> 00:32:43,462
In the pentecostal church
where I was given religion,

438
00:32:43,546 --> 00:32:46,006
it would have been said the spirit
was on you yesterday.

439
00:32:46,090 --> 00:32:48,175
- It got good to me.
- Let praises be.

440
00:32:48,259 --> 00:32:50,859
It pissed me off that on top
of everything else I gotta deal with,

441
00:32:50,886 --> 00:32:55,099
some nutjob starts killing homeless guys.
Fuck already, how many shitbowls are there?

442
00:32:55,182 --> 00:32:58,519
He's right though. You were great.
That passion was just the thing.

443
00:33:01,564 --> 00:33:03,524
- You think...
- We step out on this issue,

444
00:33:03,607 --> 00:33:05,252
it could provide some national presence...

445
00:33:05,276 --> 00:33:09,613
Didn't the governor scrap the emergency
medical and housing program last year?

446
00:33:09,697 --> 00:33:11,031
What was it, temha?

447
00:33:11,115 --> 00:33:12,324
Replaced it with t-dap,

448
00:33:12,408 --> 00:33:14,803
which cuts funding to anyone who doesn't
qualify for federal support.

449
00:33:14,827 --> 00:33:18,706
It's worse than that - he froze eligibility
by disallowing new applications,

450
00:33:18,789 --> 00:33:20,666
which put all kinda
folks out on the street.

451
00:33:20,749 --> 00:33:23,460
So we slam the republican
for sticking it to the poor.

452
00:33:23,544 --> 00:33:26,964
It plays. Nationally, you're taking up
the cause of the forgotten...

453
00:33:27,047 --> 00:33:29,133
And no one is ever in
favor of homelessness...

454
00:33:29,550 --> 00:33:32,928
Statewide, you're going up against
the fella who tore up the safety net.

455
00:33:33,846 --> 00:33:35,931
Homelessness.

456
00:33:36,015 --> 00:33:37,641
Huh.

457
00:33:38,976 --> 00:33:40,728
I'll be damned.

458
00:33:49,653 --> 00:33:52,615
- Base to 2306.
- Go ahead, Lester.

459
00:33:52,698 --> 00:33:56,035
- You see anybody using a cell phone?
- Wait one.

460
00:33:56,118 --> 00:33:59,121
Negative.

461
00:33:59,788 --> 00:34:01,957
Hold on. Somebody's here.

462
00:34:04,293 --> 00:34:05,961
Lester?

463
00:34:12,218 --> 00:34:15,763
Can't get used to how empty
this place feels nowadays.

464
00:34:15,846 --> 00:34:20,226
True, but you'd be surprised what you can
get done when no one's looking.

465
00:34:20,309 --> 00:34:23,229
You'll need to serve these.
Running out of time.

466
00:34:23,312 --> 00:34:24,772
I'll get right on it.

467
00:34:24,855 --> 00:34:27,233
There's a couple of loose ends
we should cover as well.

468
00:34:27,316 --> 00:34:29,276
- Now?
- If not now, when?

469
00:34:29,360 --> 00:34:31,612
The trial date is coming up on us fast.

470
00:34:31,695 --> 00:34:33,822
Right. But it's, uh...

471
00:34:35,824 --> 00:34:39,328
- Is it something I said?
- No, it's...

472
00:34:40,371 --> 00:34:44,250
Sydnor is bringing in a ci.
And if you're here...

473
00:34:44,333 --> 00:34:46,043
Oh, shit.

474
00:34:46,835 --> 00:34:48,337
I'm sorry...

475
00:34:50,005 --> 00:34:51,882
I'll leave you my list, ok?

476
00:34:51,966 --> 00:34:54,134
No problem. We'll get right on it.

477
00:34:54,218 --> 00:34:56,887
I'm sorry, Lester, if I was intruding.

478
00:34:58,639 --> 00:35:00,683
You couldn't know.

479
00:35:06,105 --> 00:35:07,898
So why you here?

480
00:35:08,691 --> 00:35:10,567
If this about Michael and what he into,

481
00:35:10,651 --> 00:35:12,451
y'all should know he
don't live here no more.

482
00:35:13,237 --> 00:35:15,990
Actually, I'm following
up on your man's case.

483
00:35:16,073 --> 00:35:19,034
You spoke to detective worden
when it happened.

484
00:35:23,247 --> 00:35:24,957
He was your boyfriend, right?

485
00:35:25,040 --> 00:35:26,917
When he weren't in jail...

486
00:35:27,918 --> 00:35:29,920
Father to my youngest.

487
00:35:32,339 --> 00:35:34,133
But you know how he died.

488
00:35:34,216 --> 00:35:38,262
Beaten bad. Crime of passion, as we say.

489
00:35:39,263 --> 00:35:41,307
Didn't seem like he was home long enough

490
00:35:41,390 --> 00:35:43,100
to get somebody that riled at him.

491
00:35:44,435 --> 00:35:46,353
Unless, of course, it was over you.

492
00:35:46,437 --> 00:35:48,188
You sayin' I know somethin' about that?

493
00:35:48,272 --> 00:35:50,899
Lady, let's put our cards on the table.

494
00:35:50,983 --> 00:35:54,737
I been in this game longer than a
little bit, and there's one thing I know.

495
00:35:54,820 --> 00:35:57,781
A murder like this,
there's a woman at the center of it.

496
00:35:58,115 --> 00:35:59,116
I don't know nothin'.

497
00:36:01,076 --> 00:36:03,412
You know, my gut tells me that you do.

498
00:36:04,747 --> 00:36:06,540
And I'll tell you what...

499
00:36:07,583 --> 00:36:10,502
We're gonna take a ride downtown,
let you talk to the grand jury.

500
00:36:10,586 --> 00:36:13,589
You're not straight with them,
they'll give you a material witness warrant

501
00:36:13,672 --> 00:36:17,176
and you sit over at woman's detention
for a couple of weeks.

502
00:36:17,259 --> 00:36:20,637
It's amazing what it does
for the grieving process.

503
00:36:20,721 --> 00:36:22,765
- Get your things.
- I ain't goin' nowhere.

504
00:36:22,848 --> 00:36:24,683
It's me or the wagon.

505
00:36:26,769 --> 00:36:29,063
Detective, I swear, I ain't in this.

506
00:36:30,189 --> 00:36:32,191
It ain't me you wanna talk to.

507
00:36:34,109 --> 00:36:36,653
It's the boy, he know.

508
00:36:36,737 --> 00:36:40,074
- He runnin' with them who did it.
- You just tryin' to put me off the scent.

509
00:36:40,157 --> 00:36:41,950
You gotta believe me.

510
00:36:45,871 --> 00:36:50,125
He told me devar wasn't comin' home,
'fore we even knowed he was dead.

511
00:36:52,169 --> 00:36:54,755
You said he's runnin' with them?
Runnin' with who?

512
00:36:54,838 --> 00:36:58,133
Chris, snoop, all them gangsters.
Who else doin' all the killin' around here?

513
00:37:04,306 --> 00:37:05,974
Let me see your camera.

514
00:37:11,605 --> 00:37:14,691
- Add a minute-six to your times.
- Got it.

515
00:37:14,775 --> 00:37:16,151
Here it is. Look at this.

516
00:37:17,236 --> 00:37:20,656
Single ring. Connection. Silence.

517
00:37:20,948 --> 00:37:22,699
What do you have?

518
00:37:22,783 --> 00:37:25,828
I took these three.
They're just hangin' around.

519
00:37:32,835 --> 00:37:34,920
What time did monk leave?

520
00:37:35,921 --> 00:37:38,715
1:24. Two minutes later.

521
00:37:45,013 --> 00:37:48,642
It's not what marlo's sayin',
it's what he's sendin'.

522
00:37:48,725 --> 00:37:51,603
- Look at monk.
- Yeah. Text message.

523
00:37:51,687 --> 00:37:53,772
Text? Need I remind you, detective,

524
00:37:53,856 --> 00:37:56,483
these young men are products
of Baltimore city schools.

525
00:37:57,776 --> 00:38:01,738
Besides, look how far away he's holding his
phone. Too far away to be reading a text.

526
00:38:01,822 --> 00:38:04,700
Nah, son. Pictures.

527
00:38:07,035 --> 00:38:08,704
Pictures...

528
00:38:43,780 --> 00:38:45,782
What the fuck you lookin' at?

529
00:38:46,366 --> 00:38:49,786
You know what they do, right?
They tease you, they...

530
00:38:49,870 --> 00:38:53,123
They let you get close and just
when you're about to pull the case,

531
00:38:53,207 --> 00:38:55,876
they rip the fuckin'
rug out from under you.

532
00:38:57,127 --> 00:39:01,381
I'm not lying. We got a fuckin'
serial killer on the loose.

533
00:39:03,842 --> 00:39:05,677
You didn't know that?

534
00:39:06,428 --> 00:39:08,430
It's in the goddamn paper.

535
00:39:13,936 --> 00:39:16,605
What support do I get?
One fuckin' detective.

536
00:39:18,398 --> 00:39:21,693
They wanna play their simple-ass games,
fine. But I gotta do what I gotta do.

537
00:39:21,777 --> 00:39:23,779
Excuse me.

538
00:39:26,907 --> 00:39:29,493
Mcnulty. Yeah, Oscar.

539
00:39:30,160 --> 00:39:31,662
Beautiful.

540
00:39:33,455 --> 00:39:35,749
Absolutely. Where? On my way.

541
00:40:05,112 --> 00:40:07,990
Man, you can't let it
get to you like this.

542
00:40:09,950 --> 00:40:14,079
Why don't we go buy up a bunch of toys
and take 'em to your kids?

543
00:40:14,162 --> 00:40:17,416
You ain't hearin' me. How can I go
near my people with Omar on us?

544
00:40:17,499 --> 00:40:19,126
How he gonna find out about them?

545
00:40:19,209 --> 00:40:21,628
How we find out about the blind man?

546
00:40:56,705 --> 00:40:58,248
Get.

547
00:40:58,457 --> 00:41:00,167
It's Omar!

548
00:41:05,505 --> 00:41:07,090
Ah!

549
00:41:07,174 --> 00:41:09,051
You too, shorty.

550
00:41:12,679 --> 00:41:14,681
Omar! It's Omar!

551
00:41:14,765 --> 00:41:16,808
Money a little late today.

552
00:41:29,112 --> 00:41:33,533
That buckshot in your leg should help you
explain yourself to Mario.

553
00:41:33,617 --> 00:41:36,495
As for them other two, they gonna wish
I'd've peppered 'em a bit.

554
00:41:41,083 --> 00:41:44,461
Now you make sure you tell old marlo
I burned the money.

555
00:41:44,544 --> 00:41:46,046
Cos it ain't about that paper.

556
00:41:46,129 --> 00:41:49,216
It's about me hurtin' his people
and messin' with his world.

557
00:41:49,299 --> 00:41:54,096
Tell that boy he ain't man enough
to come down to the street with Omar.

558
00:41:54,846 --> 00:41:56,014
You tell him that!

559
00:42:04,314 --> 00:42:07,067
My sergeant and two side partners
got here before me.

560
00:42:07,150 --> 00:42:10,529
Then the shift commander showed.
Now the duty officer is on his way.

561
00:42:10,612 --> 00:42:12,030
For a doa?

562
00:42:12,114 --> 00:42:14,783
Well, you and Lester
started some shit here, son.

563
00:42:14,866 --> 00:42:18,620
Now a doa call
brings everyone in a heartbeat.

564
00:43:08,211 --> 00:43:10,255
God bless.

565
00:43:19,973 --> 00:43:23,685
- Pictures?
- Photographs on cell phones.

566
00:43:24,603 --> 00:43:27,731
Now that means new PC to capture the photos

567
00:43:27,814 --> 00:43:29,941
and new equipment that could do it.

568
00:43:31,693 --> 00:43:35,322
How do I write that into
my bullshit homeless killer's mo?

569
00:43:37,324 --> 00:43:40,869
When we started this,
you said all we needed were some bugs,

570
00:43:40,952 --> 00:43:45,123
a camera or two, and in a couple of weeks,
we'd have them. That's what you said.

571
00:43:46,041 --> 00:43:48,001
So I cranked up my bullshit to pay for that

572
00:43:48,084 --> 00:43:50,837
but no, then you needed a wiretap.

573
00:43:50,921 --> 00:43:52,798
So I went along, I got you the wiretap.

574
00:43:52,881 --> 00:43:54,841
Then you ask for surveillance teams,

575
00:43:54,925 --> 00:43:57,302
but before I can get to that,
you came to me with this.

576
00:43:57,385 --> 00:43:59,429
I mean, what the fuck?

577
00:44:02,432 --> 00:44:05,852
I gotta tell you, Lester,
I don't want to hurt your feelings,

578
00:44:05,936 --> 00:44:09,481
but I can see why Daniels cringed
every time you opened your fucking mouth.

579
00:44:09,564 --> 00:44:11,650
You're a supervisor's nightmare.

580
00:44:11,733 --> 00:44:13,360
I'm just following the thread.

581
00:44:28,291 --> 00:44:31,837
Say we get you the intercept
on your pictures, will that give us marlo?

582
00:44:32,128 --> 00:44:36,383
It'll be coded, probably,
but I'm sure we can break it.

583
00:44:36,591 --> 00:44:38,510
That'll tell us how they do business,

584
00:44:38,593 --> 00:44:40,762
and usually, that's enough.

585
00:44:40,846 --> 00:44:42,722
Or not.

586
00:44:42,806 --> 00:44:45,058
But the truth is, I'm running sydnor ragged

587
00:44:45,141 --> 00:44:47,853
just staying on a couple of mopes
and monitoring calls.

588
00:44:47,936 --> 00:44:49,604
Now, when we're up on their code,

589
00:44:49,688 --> 00:44:52,858
we're gonna need more manpower
to run down a stash or a re-up.

590
00:44:52,941 --> 00:44:56,736
- We can't do it all.
- I can'tjuke this thing any more than I have.

591
00:44:56,820 --> 00:44:58,947
Last night, half the police department
turned up

592
00:44:59,030 --> 00:45:01,116
at Oscar's crime scene
before I could get there.

593
00:45:04,077 --> 00:45:05,871
We can't make another murder.

594
00:45:16,464 --> 00:45:18,091
Thanks for the milk.

595
00:45:18,174 --> 00:45:20,176
What's a donut without milk?

596
00:45:23,597 --> 00:45:27,017
So you were talking
about your second tour...

597
00:45:27,100 --> 00:45:30,186
- The bad one.
- Yeah.

598
00:45:30,270 --> 00:45:33,023
Second tour fucked me up good.
But they don't wanna hear it.

599
00:45:33,106 --> 00:45:35,066
Who doesn't?

600
00:45:35,150 --> 00:45:37,819
Mostly, it's command and the senior em's.

601
00:45:37,903 --> 00:45:40,739
They put it down that
marines don't get PTSD.

602
00:45:40,822 --> 00:45:42,866
But they do.

603
00:45:42,949 --> 00:45:45,118
Can you tell me what happened?

604
00:45:49,748 --> 00:45:51,207
Terry, can you talk about it?

605
00:45:53,835 --> 00:45:55,211
We had a month left on the tour,

606
00:45:55,295 --> 00:45:58,465
working an s-and-a
mission outside fallujah.

607
00:45:58,548 --> 00:46:01,134
I was assistant team leader.

608
00:46:01,217 --> 00:46:03,929
Our m-niner-niner-eights were
retrofitted with up-armor kits.

609
00:46:04,012 --> 00:46:06,222
M-niner-niner-eight?

610
00:46:06,306 --> 00:46:08,892
A Humvee. Sorry.

611
00:46:08,975 --> 00:46:10,810
They're big on nomenclature.

612
00:46:12,604 --> 00:46:15,523
Anyway, we finished our sweep,
headed back in, right?

613
00:46:15,607 --> 00:46:17,692
It was all good. Then, bam.

614
00:46:18,693 --> 00:46:21,237
Our lead vehicle was
hit with an elevated ied.

615
00:46:21,863 --> 00:46:24,157
The blast tore the m50 gunner in half.

616
00:46:24,240 --> 00:46:26,242
Flipped the Humvee like a matchbox car.

617
00:46:26,326 --> 00:46:28,078
Driver lost both his hands.

618
00:46:28,161 --> 00:46:30,914
Blood shooting out all over.
He's fuckin' iaughin'.

619
00:46:30,997 --> 00:46:34,000
Saying over and over, "look, ma, no hands."

620
00:46:40,632 --> 00:46:43,009
It's the laughing... I can't shake.

621
00:46:44,636 --> 00:46:45,971
Weird.

622
00:46:46,054 --> 00:46:49,057
Cos he's ok, you know?
I mean, he's better than me.

623
00:46:50,684 --> 00:46:54,688
Got himself a couple of prosthetic mitts,
eighty thousand apiece.

624
00:46:58,316 --> 00:46:59,734
Wow.

625
00:47:04,781 --> 00:47:05,865
What happened next?

626
00:47:06,866 --> 00:47:10,328
Nothing really.
We pushed out, secured the perimeter.

627
00:47:10,578 --> 00:47:14,207
Corpsman did what he could,
an' we waited for the casevac.

628
00:48:03,423 --> 00:48:05,884
I'm not looking to shit
on another guy's copy,

629
00:48:05,967 --> 00:48:07,767
I just wanted you to
know this was out there.

630
00:48:07,844 --> 00:48:09,679
I'm at a community
meeting in bel air-Edison

631
00:48:09,763 --> 00:48:13,308
to hear about school zoning and this woman
talked my ear off about this.

632
00:48:13,391 --> 00:48:16,311
- She said the kids never saw a dime.
- Hm.

633
00:48:18,229 --> 00:48:20,815
I mean, I'm hoping this is all bullshit.

634
00:48:22,067 --> 00:48:24,295
- Hey, Scott. How's it coming?
- Pretty good. You seen the art?

635
00:48:24,319 --> 00:48:26,237
Yeah. Good stuff. Listen,

636
00:48:26,321 --> 00:48:29,032
got a complaint about a story
you wrote a couple weeks ago.

637
00:48:29,115 --> 00:48:31,910
The woman who died
from an allergic reaction to seafood.

638
00:48:31,993 --> 00:48:33,286
- Remember?
- What about it?

639
00:48:33,369 --> 00:48:36,831
Lady knows the dead woman's sister says our
story made a lot of money for those kids.

640
00:48:37,082 --> 00:48:39,125
- A scholarship fund we wrote up.
- So?

641
00:48:39,209 --> 00:48:42,837
She says the sister has a history of fraud,
convictions on it.

642
00:48:43,671 --> 00:48:46,049
She says all the money went
to Atlantic city casinos

643
00:48:46,132 --> 00:48:48,760
- and kids never saw a dime.
- Christ, who the fuck...

644
00:48:48,843 --> 00:48:52,472
I know. It's probably some old biddy
talkin' about stuff she don't know,

645
00:48:52,680 --> 00:48:55,141
but maybe you should go back
and check with the family,

646
00:48:55,225 --> 00:48:57,393
see that we don't get took on this, huh?

647
00:49:02,357 --> 00:49:06,694
No, no. Not now. After you file.
Just make a couple calls, huh?

648
00:49:14,786 --> 00:49:17,163
- This is kidnapping.
- Actually, I'm not sure.

649
00:49:17,413 --> 00:49:20,834
I asked him if he wanted $100
to go some place for dinner and talk

650
00:49:21,126 --> 00:49:24,170
- and he walked to my car.
- You give him the hundred?

651
00:49:24,963 --> 00:49:26,881
Stuffed it in his jacket.

652
00:49:28,758 --> 00:49:30,885
He's fine, Lester. He's great.

653
00:49:31,928 --> 00:49:35,014
- Think he'll find his way back home?
- Eventually.

654
00:49:35,098 --> 00:49:37,976
By then, we'll be done with Mario,
we'll have shut this thing down.

655
00:49:38,059 --> 00:49:40,186
As far as what happened to this guy...

656
00:49:41,062 --> 00:49:43,148
They'll write it off as
some fraternity prank.

657
00:49:44,732 --> 00:49:47,777
- Does he know we're cops?
- No.

658
00:49:47,861 --> 00:49:50,301
Even if he figures it out,
who's gonna believe him? He's nuts.

659
00:49:50,363 --> 00:49:53,158
- How do you know he's nuts?
- First of all, just look at him.

660
00:49:53,241 --> 00:49:56,953
He's fucking bouncing off the walls.
Second of all... I got his scrip.

661
00:49:57,036 --> 00:49:59,914
I called the university er.
It's an anti-psychotic.

662
00:50:02,750 --> 00:50:04,127
I took his ID,

663
00:50:04,377 --> 00:50:08,256
I'll scratch his name off the scrip
and leave him with this...

664
00:50:09,174 --> 00:50:12,927
I got that one from the first
homeless death Oscar gave us.

665
00:50:13,011 --> 00:50:15,388
The one that was too rigored.
Donald somebody or other.

666
00:50:15,597 --> 00:50:18,099
It had him in a Cleveland, Ohio shelter.

667
00:50:18,766 --> 00:50:22,645
Mcnulty, you are deserving
of serious psychological study.

668
00:50:22,729 --> 00:50:25,023
You need PC to intercept cell phone photos.

669
00:50:25,106 --> 00:50:27,150
Well, here it is, right here.

670
00:50:27,233 --> 00:50:29,152
We send photos of this guy

671
00:50:29,235 --> 00:50:31,154
all ribboned up from a dry cell phone

672
00:50:31,237 --> 00:50:34,657
to that goofy reporter, along with
a message bitching about his stories.

673
00:50:34,949 --> 00:50:37,911
"I ain't no pervert," or whatever.
Now, the killer says,

674
00:50:37,994 --> 00:50:41,122
you ain't gonna find no more bodies.
Only photos of the victims...

675
00:50:41,748 --> 00:50:43,750
Before they disappear.

676
00:50:48,046 --> 00:50:51,674
Look at this poor sucker.
I don't believe we're gonna do this.

677
00:50:51,758 --> 00:50:55,637
He disappears, the city goes batshit.
You get your photo intercepts,

678
00:50:55,720 --> 00:50:57,656
and when we need to
run down one of marlo's re-ups,

679
00:50:57,680 --> 00:50:59,682
you got all the manpower you need.

680
00:50:59,766 --> 00:51:01,935
- And marlo falls.
- Falls hard.

681
00:51:25,166 --> 00:51:28,253
Don't fucking tell me
you mislabeled this, too.

682
00:51:28,336 --> 00:51:31,798
I want comparisons between known suspects

683
00:51:31,881 --> 00:51:33,591
and the DNA from this scene.

684
00:51:33,925 --> 00:51:37,262
By the looks of it,
we got a whole lot of DNA outta this mess.

685
00:51:37,345 --> 00:51:40,431
- Now, motherfucker. Right now.
- Top of my list.

686
00:51:41,057 --> 00:51:44,352
As soon as we work through
all the trace from the homeless killings.

687
00:51:45,353 --> 00:51:46,854
That's the priority, bunk.

688
00:51:49,190 --> 00:51:53,194
- The homeless killings.
- Everything is backed up behind that, sorry.

689
00:51:53,611 --> 00:51:55,905
Your boy mcnulty has
everyone's attention right now.

690
00:52:12,672 --> 00:52:14,674
So it's Larry, huh?

691
00:52:16,884 --> 00:52:20,888
Ok, Larry. You're with good people here.
It's all gonna be great.

692
00:52:23,641 --> 00:52:27,645
You're gonna like this place.
It's warm, they got nice beds.

693
00:52:29,272 --> 00:52:33,276
And best of all, I gave you
cash moneyjust for walking in the door.

694
00:52:37,905 --> 00:52:39,574
Come on, Larry.

695
00:52:41,701 --> 00:52:43,953
It's gonna be fine. I promise.

696
00:52:53,588 --> 00:52:55,882
You feel up for trying Clay yourself?

697
00:52:56,424 --> 00:53:00,470
I mean, it's been a while since
you tried a criminal case personally.

